---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ConceptPageHero from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPageHero.astro';
import ConceptPager from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPager.astro';
import { getConcept } from '../../lib/concepts';

const c = getConcept('relativity');
---

<Layout title={`${c.title} | Identity Engineering`}>
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<ConceptPageHero
			scene={c.scene}
			tag={`${c.tag} · ${c.layerLabel}`}
			title={c.title}
			lede={c.blurb}
			scrollHint={c.scrollHint}
		/>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Interactive layer</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">
					Identity is not absolute.
				</h2>
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Relativity</strong> states that identity exists only in relation to
					another observing identity. This is the bridge from the single-identity geometry
					(Time, Mass, Curvature, Rotation) to the interactive field.
				</p>
				<p>
					Measurement and recognition are not afterthoughts. Continuity is observed through change,
					especially when AI can copy states and mirror surfaces. What remains is the <strong class="text-white/80">differential history</strong> as seen (and contested) between observers.
				</p>
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/30 p-6">
					<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/40 mb-3">Frame principle</div>
					<p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
						Identity continuity claims are always frame-bound:
						<code class="text-violet-300">same-for-observer-A</code> can differ from
						<code class="text-violet-300">same-for-observer-B</code> when histories, incentives, and evidence differ.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Implications</div>
				<ul class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Observer-dependence:</strong> how our stem is read depends on the other’s frame
						(their mass, curvature, vision).
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Mutual definition:</strong> relationships co-produce identity geometry.
						Isolation is an idealization, not the default ontology.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">AI-era stress test:</strong> when copies are cheap, the question
						“same as whom, for whom, under what observation?” becomes central.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Engineering work:</strong> Design for legible differentials under observation.
					Make the State Differential transparent enough that another identity (human or artificial)
					can track sameness-as-trajectory without freezing us into a copyable snapshot.
				</p>
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/30 p-6">
					<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/40 mb-3">Practical probes</div>
					<ul class="space-y-3 text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
						<li>Which observer groups matter most for my continuity claims?</li>
						<li>What evidence do they need to track real continuity?</li>
						<li>Where am I still over-relying on static, copyable signals?</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<p class="text-white/40 text-base">
					Note: Questions as Probes (measurement instruments) remain part of the broader practice layer.
					On the website they currently share visual language with Relativity’s observational theme.
					The interactive layer will keep evolving.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ConceptPager id="relativity" />
	</main>
</Layout>
